<dl id="n38020e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38020e">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38020e"> 20(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> la belle alliance <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n38020e"><li>FW 144.12 </li><li><a href="../../flex/fa/lexfa.htm#n38020e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/fa/l39fa.htm#n38020e">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n38020e">MS BL 47475-272</ms> </li><li>JJA 47:283 <a name="fad6y" href="../../FF/fdra/fda.htm#fad6y">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/fa/fad6.htm#n38020e">Draft: I.6&sect;1.6</a>+ </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: Fr. <i>La belle alliance</i>: the beautiful alliance (Fr. <i>alliance</i> can mean &lsquo;union&rsquo; or &lsquo;wedding ring&rsquo;). It was the name of the farm where Napoleon&apos;s headquarters were situated during the Battle of Waterloo. The Prussians called the battle of Waterloo &lsquo;La Belle Alliance&rsquo;, as the centre of the French lines was at La Belle Alliance Inn. </mm> </dd></dl>
